<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910628-0044</DOCNO><DOCID>910628-0044.</DOCID><HL>   Diagnostic Sciences   To Acquire Norton   In $4.2 Million Deal</HL><DATE>06/28/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4B</SO><CO>   DSIC</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)CONSUMER NON-CYCLICAL (NCY)</MS><IN>OIL DRILLING AND EXPLORATION (DRL)OIL EQUIPMENT, SERVICES, PLATFORM SUPPLIERS (EQS)HEALTH CARE PROVIDERS, MEDICINE, DENTISTRY (HEA)OIL EQUIPMENT AND SERVICES (OIE)PETROLEUM (PET)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   NEW YORK -- Diagnostic Sciences Inc. agreed to acquireNorton Drilling Co.'s shares outstanding in a stock swapvalued at a minimum $4.2 million.   Norton, a privately held company based in Lubbock, Texas,owns and operates 13 drilling rigs in the Southwest and hadrevenue of $21.4 million in 1990. Diagnostic owns and managesa magnetic resonance imaging center in Huntington, N.Y., andrecently entered the wholesale flower business when itacquired Sunny's Plants in February. The acquisition willsharply boost its revenue, which was $4.76 million on a proforma basis for the fiscal year ended Nov. 30.</LP><TEXT>   Under the agreement, Diagnostic will issue between 4.16million new shares of its common stock if its stock price isabove $1 and 5.16 million new shares if its stock goes below$1. Diagnostic will also issue an additional one million to1.25 million shares to Norton depending on future earnings.   The total transaction could give Norton holders almost 20%of Diagnostic's outstanding common. In addition, DiagnosticSciences' board would be expanded by three directors andNorton Drilling would name those directors.   Gerry Angulo, Diagnostic's chief executive officer, saidthe acquisition will give Diagnostic &quot;over $30 million inannual revenue this year, $20 million in assets and a bookvalue of over $10 million.&quot;</TEXT></DOC>